d 'QUASICOINT': module to perform Quasi-Cointegration Analysis without Unit Roots 
d
d	quasicoint implements the quasi-cointegration framework of
d Duffy & Simons (2023), which extends standard    cointegration
d analysis to settings where the dominant autoregressive roots may
d be near but not exactly equal    to unity.	The problem.
d Elliott (1998) showed that standard efficient estimators of
d cointegrating relationships	 (FM-OLS, DOLS, Johansen ML) suffer
d severe size distortions when roots are near but not exactly at
d unity —    even within an O(n{c -1}) neighbourhood that is
d empirically indistinguishable from exact unit roots.	  The
d solution. Rather than defining cointegration in terms of
d integration orders — which becomes vacuous	  without exact
d unit roots — Duffy & Simons identify long-run equilibrium
d relationships via the {bf:relative	decay rates of impulse
d responses}. The resulting quasi-cointegrating space (QCS)
d coincides exactly with the	standard cointegrating space when
d unit roots are present, but remains meaningful when they are not. d
d KW: cointegration
d KW: unit roots
d KW: quasi-integrated
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260509
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
